<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta http-equiv="X-UA-Compatible" content="IE=edge">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>3 Ways to apply css</title>
    <!-- external css is used to describe style of all web pages if it has to be connected via link -->
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="./style.css">
    <!-- internal css is weitten in head tag and can be used to describe whole web page -->
    <style>
        /* Here, h2 selector will apply style of every h2 in this page */
        h2{
            color: aquamarine;
            background-color: black;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <!-- inline css is written in open tag  of an element and describes style for that element -->
    <h1 style="color: red;
    background: cornflowerblue;
    text-align: center;">Hello World</h1>
    <p>Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet consectetur, adipisicing elit. Minima quos a dolorem amet cum non esse. Laboriosam, accusantium. In tempore recusandae quos saepe laboriosam accusamus inventore iure dolorum quibusdam. Sint?</p>
    <h2>This is Us</h2>
    <h2>This is also Us</h2>
</body>
</html>
